c({"name": "jquery.model.validations", "type": "page", "comment": "<p>In many apps, it's important to validate data before sending it to the server. \nThe jquery/model/validations plugin provides validations on models.</p>\n\n<h2>Example</h2>\n\n<p>To use validations, you need to call a validate method on the Model class.\nThe best place to do this is in a Class's init function.</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>$.Model(\"Contact\",{\n    init : function(){\n        // validates that birthday is in the future\n        this.validate(\"birthday\",function(){\n            if(this.birthday > new Date){\n                return \"your birthday needs to be in the past\"\n            }\n        })\n    }\n},{});</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Demo</h2>\n\n<p>Click a person's name to update their birthday.  If you put the date\nin the future, say the year 2525, it will report back an error.</p>\n\n<div class='demo_wrapper' data-demo-src='jquery/model/validations/validations.html'></div> ", "title": "Validations", "plugin": "jquery/model/validations", "download": "http://jmvcsite.heroku.com/pluginify?plugins[]=jquery/model/validations/validations.js", "test": "jquery/model/validations/qunit.html", "parents": ["jQuery.Model"], "src": "jquery/model/validations/validations.js", "line": 0, "children": ["jQuery.Model.static.validate", "jQuery.Model.static.validate", "jQuery.Model.static.validationMessages", "jQuery.Model.static.validationMessages", "jQuery.Model.static.validateFormatOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateFormatOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateInclusionOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateInclusionOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateLengthOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateLengthOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validatePresenceOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validatePresenceOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateRangeOf", "jQuery.Model.static.validateRangeOf"]})